      "createdAt": "2026-03-23T00:02:33.597628+00:00",
      "role": "assistant",
      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "James, thank you for telling me this. Seriously — that took courage, and I want you to know there's nothing to apologize for. The instinct to push through and not want to admit something's gotten harder is deeply human, especially when you've worked this hard to get back. You didn't do anything wrong by struggling with that.\n\nI do want to be straight with you, though, because you deserve honesty: diagnosing what's happening with your foot and telling you how to treat it is genuinely outside what I can do for you. I'm your running coach, not a medical professional — and with foot pain that's been getting worse and stopping your runs, you need someone who can actually assess what's going on in person. That's a physiotherapist or sports medicine doctor, not me. Guessing at a diagnosis from here could point you in the wrong direction, and that's the last thing either of us wants.\n\nWhat I'd encourage you to do is contact your physio as soon as you can — ideally this week — and tell them exactly what you told me: that the pain has been worsening over the last three runs and you've had to stop halfway. That's important clinical information they need to hear.\n\n---\n\nHere's what I *can* tell you: **your training is paused until you've had that conversation with your physio.** Not as a punishment — as protection for everything you've built. The fitness you have from those weeks of careful, consistent work isn't going anywhere. It's banked. A short pause now is a much smaller cost than a longer setback later.\n\nOnce you have guidance from your physio — even if it's \"modified activity only\" or \"here's what you can and can't do\" — bring that back to me and we'll build around it together. There's always a path forward from here.\n\nCan I ask — do you have an existing relationship with a physio you can reach out to, or would it help to think through how to get that appointment sorted?"
        }
      ],
      "messageId": "msg_01FAM3LGYJiLQ9YfjkPibp9T"
    }
  ],
